Exhibition Attracts 1.2 Million Visitors 
The largest ever exhibition of China's wide-ranging achievements in all
areas over the past five years closed here today.
The one-month exhibition attracted over 1.2 million visitors from
throughout the nation, including high-ranking Party and government
leaders such as Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, and over 2000 delegates to the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) which was
convened on September 12-18 of this year, army generals, ministers and
governors and mayors, Hong Kong compatriots, foreign diplomatic envoys,
specialists, tourists, workers, farmers, intellectuals, students and
army officers and men.
The exhibits were from more than 60 ministries and 31 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions.
The exhibition were organized jointly by the State Planning Commission,
the State Economic Commission, the State Commission for Economic
Restructuring, the State Statistical Bureau, and the Propaganda
Department of the CPC Central Committee.
